column5: Wondering who is planning on going this weekend ?  TB
We are going on Saturday.  Joey
i'll be there with the family  Nick
I was going to go tomorrow but figure i have to be tight with my money as im buying a new truck.  I was pumped up for this since Christmas
Be there all day Saturday... look for me Fishontario booth or walking around
Any one know if they still have free parking at Ontario Place still  Hate having to pay to park at that place
Last time I drove by there....about a month ago... it said $5 !

Can't help you on Ontario Place parking, except that their lots were all empty close to the show. 12 skins for parking. I just got back a half hour ago.  I'd say it's slightly better than a lot of recent ones with regards to decent sale items.  Some good deals on quality baits and lures.  Everything else seemed per norm.  Hot buy - Gulp $18ea. I won't say who, but they're in Hamilton.

$ 5 at Ont place  we bought 2 ice packs folding scissors two flint/steel firestarters sunshine girl calander ( son's purhcase) $3.50 bottle of water  Met one of Pikeie s instructors at the Sault college booth , chatted with the Minn Kota rep ( clueless) and a buddy at OFAH . Worth an afternoon  TB
Thank God there wasn't a Starbucks in there....

Had planned on going for the longest time.tommorow with sinns........But now tommorow is my BIG day so now i cant make it....  Have fun everyone & just remember to pack a bottled water in your pocket or purse....
I'll be there tomorrow , checking out fishing booth Blake is hooking me up ooh yea!
